name: Spinach Muenster Quiche
author: DOREENB
summary: This cheese crusted quiche is great with a salad and crusty bread!
ingredients: 2 (10 ounce) packages frozen chopped spinach, thawed and drained
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Line a quiche dish or 9 inch pie pan with the 8 ounces of Muenster cheese slices
Carefully press all of the water out of the spinach and place it in a large mixing bowl
Add eggs, Parmesan cheese, cream cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder; stir well
Spoon mixture into pan and top with remaining cheese slices
Bake in preheated oven for 35 minutes and allow to set up for 10 minutes before serving
Decrease oven temperature by 25 degrees F if using glass pie dish
